OL,6,FThere was government acknowledgement,
OL,7,Fin both the House of Commons and House
OL,8,Fof Lords in the late 1950s, that the
OL,9,Feffects of the use of DES could be
OL,10,F'seriously toxic' when ingested or
OL,11,Finhaled by humans in even the smallest
OL,12,Famount, yet it was still used for
OL,13,Fyears as a lactation suppressant.
OL,15,FIn 1959, an MP in the Commons warned
OL,16,Fabout the risk of exposure to farmer
OL,17,Fworkers who were using it to fatten
OL,18,Flivestock.
