OL,6,FThen in 1961 in the House of Lords,
OL,7,FLord Douglas of Barlockwas concerned
OL,8,Fthat diethylstilbestrol used in
OL,9,Ffarming could get into the food chain,
OL,10,Fstating 'it has been authoritatively
OL,11,Fstated that it may have something to
OL,12,Fdo with causing cancer or leukemia.'
OL,14,FThe same concern wasn't shown for
OL,15,Fwomen in mother and baby homes. The
OL,16,Fdrug was still used in the UK for
OL,17,Fyears after these stark warnings.
