OL,6,FThe UK government has never issued a
OL,7,Fformal apology to those impacted by
OL,8,Fthe forced adoption scandal, despite
OL,9,Fthe devolved nations and countries
OL,10,Faround the world offering recognition
OL,11,Ffor the role their governments played
OL,12,Fin the practice for decades.
OL,14,FAdoptees and mothers alike are calling
OL,15,Ffor an apology, and for some now in
OL,16,Ftheir 70s and 80s time is truly
OL,17,Frunning out.
